{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":562,"text":"Eric Berlow: I'm an ecologist, and Sean's a physicist,"},{"time":3623,"text":"and we both study complex networks."},{"time":5731,"text":"And we met a couple years ago when we discovered"},{"time":7566,"text":"that we had both given a short TED Talk"},{"time":9566,"text":"about the ecology of war,"},{"time":11869,"text":"and we realized that we were connected"},{"time":13316,"text":"by the ideas we shared before we ever met."},{"time":16134,"text":"And then we thought, you know, there are thousands"},{"time":17690,"text":"of other talks out there, especially TEDx Talks,"},{"time":19804,"text":"that are popping up all over the world."},{"time":22015,"text":"How are they connected,"},{"time":22938,"text":"and what does that global conversation look like?"},{"time":24948,"text":"So Sean's going to tell you a little bit about how we did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27758,"text":"Sean Gourley: Exactly. So we took 24,000 TEDx Talks"},{"time":31525,"text":"from around the world, 147 different countries,"},{"time":34571,"text":"and we took these talks and we wanted to find"},{"time":36694,"text":"the mathematical structures that underly"},{"time":38734,"text":"the ideas behind them."},{"time":40456,"text":"And we wanted to do that so we could see how"},{"time":41826,"text":"they connected with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43879,"text":"And so, of course, if you're going to do this kind of stuff,"},{"time":45555,"text":"you need a lot of data."},{"time":46511,"text":"So the data that you've got is a great thing called YouTube,"},{"time":50197,"text":"and we can go down and basically pull"},{"time":51965,"text":"all the open information from YouTube,"},{"time":54232,"text":"all the comments, all the views, who's watching it,"},{"time":56581,"text":"where are they watching it, what are they saying in the comments."},{"time":59360,"text":"But we can also pull up, using speech-to-text translation,"},{"time":62652,"text":"we can pull the entire transcript,"},{"time":64780,"text":"and that works even for people with kind of funny accents like myself."},{"time":67460,"text":"So we can take their transcript"},{"time":69566,"text":"and actually do some pretty cool things."},{"time":71664,"text":"We can take natural language processing algorithms"},{"time":73824,"text":"to kind of read through with a computer, line by line,"},{"time":76453,"text":"extracting key concepts from this."},{"time":78812,"text":"And we take those key concepts and they sort of form"},{"time":81337,"text":"this mathematical structure of an idea."},{"time":84902,"text":"And we call that the meme-ome."},{"time":86659,"text":"And the meme-ome, you know, quite simply,"},{"time":88810,"text":"is the mathematics that underlies an idea,"},{"time":91236,"text":"and we can do some pretty interesting analysis with it,"},{"time":93168,"text":"which I want to share with you now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95149,"text":"So each idea has its own meme-ome,"},{"time":97339,"text":"and each idea is unique with that,"},{"time":99290,"text":"but of course, ideas, they borrow from each other,"},{"time":101778,"text":"they kind of steal sometimes,"},{"time":102962,"text":"and they certainly build on each other,"},{"time":104789,"text":"and we can go through mathematically"},{"time":106405,"text":"and take the meme-ome from one talk"},{"time":108245,"text":"and compare it to the meme-ome from every other talk,"},{"time":110699,"text":"and if there's a similarity between the two of them,"},{"time":112672,"text":"we can create a link and represent that as a graph,"},{"time":115922,"text":"just like Eric and I are connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118316,"text":"So that's theory, that's great."},{"time":119710,"text":"Let's see how it works in actual practice."},{"time":122236,"text":"So what we've got here now is the global footprint"},{"time":125024,"text":"of all the TEDx Talks over the last four years"},{"time":127317,"text":"exploding out around the world"},{"time":128867,"text":"from New York all the way down to little old New Zealand in the corner."},{"time":132196,"text":"And what we did on this is we analyzed the top 25 percent of these,"},{"time":136031,"text":"and we started to see where the connections occurred,"},{"time":138565,"text":"where they connected with each other."},{"time":140102,"text":"Cameron Russell talking about image and beauty"},{"time":141976,"text":"connected over into Europe."},{"time":143551,"text":"We've got a bigger conversation about Israel and Palestine"},{"time":145963,"text":"radiating outwards from the Middle East."},{"time":148218,"text":"And we've got something a little broader"},{"time":149516,"text":"like big data with a truly global footprint"},{"time":151672,"text":"reminiscent of a conversation"},{"time":153851,"text":"that is happening everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155867,"text":"So from this, we kind of run up against the limits"},{"time":158040,"text":"of what we can actually do with a geographic projection,"},{"time":160570,"text":"but luckily, computer technology allows us to go out"},{"time":162622,"text":"into multidimensional space."},{"time":164168,"text":"So we can take in our network projection"},{"time":166043,"text":"and apply a physics engine to this,"},{"time":167793,"text":"and the similar talks kind of smash together,"},{"time":169678,"text":"and the different ones fly apart,"},{"time":171682,"text":"and what we're left with is something quite beautiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173754,"text":"EB: So I want to just point out here that every node is a talk,"},{"time":176711,"text":"they're linked if they share similar ideas,"},{"time":179300,"text":"and that comes from a machine reading"},{"time":181384,"text":"of entire talk transcripts,"},{"time":183451,"text":"and then all these topics that pop out,"},{"time":185682,"text":"they're not from tags and keywords."},{"time":187472,"text":"They come from the network structure"},{"time":189197,"text":"of interconnected ideas. Keep going."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191365,"text":"SG: Absolutely. So I got a little quick on that,"},{"time":193387,"text":"but he's going to slow me down."},{"time":194862,"text":"We've got education connected to storytelling"},{"time":196896,"text":"triangulated next to social media."},{"time":198539,"text":"You've got, of course, the human brain right next to healthcare,"},{"time":201014,"text":"which you might expect,"},{"time":202400,"text":"but also you've got video games, which is sort of adjacent,"},{"time":204795,"text":"as those two spaces interface with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207535,"text":"But I want to take you into one cluster"},{"time":209070,"text":"that's particularly important to me, and that's the environment."},{"time":211938,"text":"And I want to kind of zoom in on that"},{"time":213431,"text":"and see if we can get a little more resolution."},{"time":215794,"text":"So as we go in here, what we start to see,"},{"time":218141,"text":"apply the physics engine again,"},{"time":219645,"text":"we see what's one conversation"},{"time":221321,"text":"is actually composed of many smaller ones."},{"time":223881,"text":"The structure starts to emerge"},{"time":225810,"text":"where we see a kind of fractal behavior"},{"time":227880,"text":"of the words and the language that we use"},{"time":229499,"text":"to describe the things that are important to us"},{"time":231201,"text":"all around this world."},{"time":232634,"text":"So you've got food economy and local food at the top,"},{"time":234966,"text":"you've got greenhouse gases, solar and nuclear waste."},{"time":237685,"text":"What you're getting is a range of smaller conversations,"},{"time":240316,"text":"each connected to each other through the ideas"},{"time":242617,"text":"and the language they share,"},{"time":243918,"text":"creating a broader concept of the environment."},{"time":246368,"text":"And of course, from here, we can go"},{"time":247900,"text":"and zoom in and see, well, what are young people looking at?"},{"time":251434,"text":"And they're looking at energy technology and nuclear fusion."},{"time":253779,"text":"This is their kind of resonance"},{"time":255453,"text":"for the conversation around the environment."},{"time":257859,"text":"If we split along gender lines,"},{"time":259758,"text":"we can see females resonating heavily"},{"time":261745,"text":"with food economy, but also out there in hope and optimism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265390,"text":"And so there's a lot of exciting stuff we can do here,"},{"time":267872,"text":"and I'll throw to Eric for the next part."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269634,"text":"EB: Yeah, I mean, just to point out here,"},{"time":271236,"text":"you cannot get this kind of perspective"},{"time":272774,"text":"from a simple tag search on YouTube."},{"time":276134,"text":"Let's now zoom back out to the entire global conversation"},{"time":280322,"text":"out of environment, and look at all the talks together."},{"time":282856,"text":"Now often, when we're faced with this amount of content,"},{"time":285783,"text":"we do a couple of things to simplify it."},{"time":288214,"text":"We might just say, well,"},{"time":289528,"text":"what are the most popular talks out there?"},{"time":292357,"text":"And a few rise to the surface."},{"time":293754,"text":"There's a talk about gratitude."},{"time":295582,"text":"There's another one about personal health and nutrition."},{"time":298926,"text":"And of course, there's got to be one about porn, right?"},{"time":301855,"text":"And so then we might say, well, gratitude, that was last year."},{"time":305089,"text":"What's trending now? What's the popular talk now?"},{"time":307611,"text":"And we can see that the new, emerging, top trending topic"},{"time":310932,"text":"is about digital privacy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313598,"text":"So this is great. It simplifies things."},{"time":315291,"text":"But there's so much creative content"},{"time":317118,"text":"that's just buried at the bottom."},{"time":319039,"text":"And I hate that. How do we bubble stuff up to the surface"},{"time":322357,"text":"that's maybe really creative and interesting?"},{"time":324815,"text":"Well, we can go back to the network structure of ideas"},{"time":327746,"text":"to do that."},{"time":329176,"text":"Remember, it's that network structure"},{"time":331290,"text":"that is creating these emergent topics,"},{"time":333558,"text":"and let's say we could take two of them,"},{"time":335073,"text":"like cities and genetics, and say, well, are there any talks"},{"time":338120,"text":"that creatively bridge these two really different disciplines."},{"time":340689,"text":"And that's -- Essentially, this kind of creative remix"},{"time":342964,"text":"is one of the hallmarks of innovation."},{"time":344804,"text":"Well here's one by Jessica Green"},{"time":346410,"text":"about the microbial ecology of buildings."},{"time":348789,"text":"It's literally defining a new field."},{"time":350799,"text":"And we could go back to those topics and say, well,"},{"time":352902,"text":"what talks are central to those conversations?"},{"time":355670,"text":"In the cities cluster, one of the most central"},{"time":357360,"text":"was one by Mitch Joachim about ecological cities,"},{"time":361312,"text":"and in the genetics cluster,"},{"time":363032,"text":"we have a talk about synthetic biology by Craig Venter."},{"time":366225,"text":"These are talks that are linking many talks within their discipline."},{"time":369578,"text":"We could go the other direction and say, well,"},{"time":371421,"text":"what are talks that are broadly synthesizing"},{"time":373693,"text":"a lot of different kinds of fields."},{"time":375141,"text":"We used a measure of ecological diversity to get this."},{"time":377674,"text":"Like, a talk by Steven Pinker on the history of violence,"},{"time":380410,"text":"very synthetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381590,"text":"And then, of course, there are talks that are so unique"},{"time":383668,"text":"they're kind of out in the stratosphere, in their own special place,"},{"time":386758,"text":"and we call that the Colleen Flanagan index."},{"time":389272,"text":"And if you don't know Colleen, she's an artist,"},{"time":392306,"text":"and I asked her, \"Well, what's it like out there"},{"time":393849,"text":"in the stratosphere of our idea space?\""},{"time":395521,"text":"And apparently it smells like bacon."},{"time":398776,"text":"I wouldn't know."},{"time":400567,"text":"So we're using these network motifs"},{"time":402815,"text":"to find talks that are unique,"},{"time":404001,"text":"ones that are creatively synthesizing a lot of different fields,"},{"time":406711,"text":"ones that are central to their topic,"},{"time":408370,"text":"and ones that are really creatively bridging disparate fields."},{"time":411744,"text":"Okay? We never would have found those with our obsession"},{"time":413846,"text":"with what's trending now."},{"time":416159,"text":"And all of this comes from the architecture of complexity,"},{"time":419045,"text":"or the patterns of how things are connected."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422005,"text":"SG: So that's exactly right."},{"time":423630,"text":"We've got ourselves in a world"},{"time":426109,"text":"that's massively complex,"},{"time":428153,"text":"and we've been using algorithms to kind of filter it down"},{"time":431020,"text":"so we can navigate through it."},{"time":432806,"text":"And those algorithms, whilst being kind of useful,"},{"time":435144,"text":"are also very, very narrow, and we can do better than that,"},{"time":438620,"text":"because we can realize that their complexity is not random."},{"time":441186,"text":"It has mathematical structure,"},{"time":443140,"text":"and we can use that mathematical structure"},{"time":444943,"text":"to go and explore things like the world of ideas"},{"time":447157,"text":"to see what's being said, to see what's not being said,"},{"time":450157,"text":"and to be a little bit more human"},{"time":451564,"text":"and, hopefully, a little smarter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453431,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454397,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}